DNA test in children
If you have the hereditary predisposition, all your children are eligible for a DNA test. A DNA test in children under the age of 10 is usually not necessary because HCM usually develops later. Because HCM can sometimes cause symptoms in teenagers, it is advisable for children from about 10 years of age to consider a DNA test. To discuss a possible DNA test, your child can be referred to our outpatient clinic by us or the GP. To help you and your child with this as best as possible, you and your child will always be seen at the Clinical Genetics Outpatient Clinic in the hospital during a DNA test in childhood. After a conversation with a clinical geneticist (hereditary doctor) and social worker, you can choose whether or not to do a DNA test on your child.

