The DNA-poli (ed: the platform) is there to inform you and help you make your choice. If you want a DNA test, this is how it works:
Step 1: We will ask you later what your preference is. If you choose, a short video call with a healthcare provider will follow for confirmation and to answer any questions.
Step 2: You will then receive a package with tubes for taking blood and a form. This will be sent to you by post.
Step 3: You can take this package with you to a blood test clinic near you. You can have blood drawn there.
Step 4: The blood test clinic sends the blood tubes to us. We perform the DNA test in the laboratory of the university hospital where your family member was also tested.
Step 5: The results will be known after approximately 6 weeks. You can get the results via the DNA clinic, in your own portal. If you have any questions, you can then make a telephone appointment. If you prefer, we can also discuss the results with you by telephone. You can indicate this during the conversation with the care provider.

